ith valid kubeconfig\n  Line 31: - **WHEN** the Agentd idle cleanup controller starts\n  Line 35: #### Scenario: AR-018-001-B — Controller initializes informers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n  Line 44: ### AR-018-002: Idle timeout configuration\n  Line 48: #### Scenario: AR-018-002-A — Controller uses default idle timeout when env not set\n  Line 54: #### Scenario: AR-018-002-B — Controller uses custom idle timeout from environment\n  Line 60: #### Scenario: AR-018-002-C — Controller uses custom check interval from environment\n  Line 68: ### AR-018-003: Idle detection for AgentRuntime\n  Line 72: #### Scenario: AR-018-003-A — AgentRuntime is idle when no recent activity\n  Line 78: #### Scenario: AR-018-003-B — AgentRuntime is not idle when recently active\n  Line 84: #### Scenario: AR-018-003-C — AgentRuntime without activity timestamp uses creation time\n  Line 92: ### AR-018-004: Idle detection for CodeInterpreter\n  Line 96: #### Scenario: AR-018-004-A — CodeInterpreter is idle when no recent activity\n  Line 102: #### Scenario: AR-018-004-B — CodeInterpreter is not idle when recently active\n  Line 110: ### AR-018-005: Idle resource cleanup\n  Line 114: #### Scenario: AR-018-005-A — Controller deletes idle AgentRuntime\n  Line 121: #### Scenario: AR-018-005-B — Controller deletes idle CodeInterpreter\n  Line 128: #### Scenario: AR-018-005-C — Cleanup continues when delete fails for one resource\n  Line 137: ### AR-018-006: Periodic cleanup loop\n  Line 141: #### Scenario: AR-018-006-A — Cleanup runs at configured interval\n  Line 147: #### Scenario: AR-018-006-B — Cleanup stops when stop channel is closed\n  Line 153: #### Scenario: AR-018-006-C — Cleanup processes all namespaces by default\n  Line 161: ### AR-018-007: Graceful shutdown\n  Line 165: #### Scenario: AR-018-007-A — Controller uses grace period before deletion\n  Line 172: #### Scenario: AR-018-007-B — Controller logs cleanup actions\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bail